UGHH THE CAPITALIZATION IN THE TITLE IS WEIRD
A lot of these photos are really old, they were released in January. However I do see some new ones, mostly from the rover itself, cool!
Why is it the surface in those pictures looks drastically browner? Different camera settings?

Why is it the surface in those pictures looks drastically browner? Different camera settings?

Probably a combination of camera settings and landing site. Chang'e is in one of the maria while all apollo missions landed in either the highlands or a maria border at best IIRC.
